content: Gross profit increased 41% to $126 million in the fourth quarter compared to $89 million in the prior year driven by the increase in the higher-margin service, parts and other sales, as well as the shift in the mix of the size of the boats sold. Full year 2022 gross profit increased 55% to $554 million, driven by the shift in the mix of size of the boats sold as well as significant increase in the higher-margin service and parts and other sales.
